
To expand your application to allow a logged-in user to add new blogs, you can follow these steps. Building upon the previous example, I'll add the necessary components for adding new blogs.

Create a New Blog Form:
You can create a form for adding new blogs. This form should include fields for the blog title, content, and any other relevant information. Here's an example of the HTML structure for the form:

html
Copy code
<div id="blogForm" style="display: none;">
  <h2>Add New Blog</h2>
  <form id="newBlogForm">
    <label for="blogTitle">Title:</label>
    <input type="text" id="blogTitle" required><br>
    <label for="blogContent">Content:</label>
    <textarea id="blogContent" required></textarea><br>
    <button type="submit">Add Blog</button>
  </form>
</div>
Show the New Blog Form for Logged-In Users:
Modify the showLoggedInUI function to display the new blog form when a user is logged in.

javascript
Copy code
function showLoggedInUI(username) {
  // Display user information and the "Logout" button
  document.getElementById('userGreeting').textContent = `Hello, ${username}!`;
  document.getElementById('loginForm').style.display = 'none';
  document.getElementById('logoutButton').style.display = 'block';
  document.getElementById('blogForm').style.display = 'block'; // Show the new blog form
}
Handle Form Submission:
Implement JavaScript to handle the form submission. When the user submits the form, you can collect the blog data and perform any necessary actions (e.g., sending the data to a server).

javascript
Copy code
document.getElementById('newBlogForm').addEventListener('submit', function (e) {
  e.preventDefault();

  const blogTitle = document.getElementById('blogTitle').value;
  const blogContent = document.getElementById('blogContent').value;

  // Perform actions like sending data to the server, saving to a database, etc.
  // After successfully adding the blog, you can update the UI as needed.

  // For example, you can clear the form and display a success message:
  document.getElementById('blogTitle').value = '';
  document.getElementById('blogContent').value = '';
  alert('Blog added successfully!');
});
Update the UI After Adding a Blog:
After successfully adding a blog, you might want to update the UI to show the newly added blog or refresh the blog list.

javascript
Copy code
// Function to update the blog list
function updateBlogList(newBlog) {
  // Add the new blog to the list of blogs in the UI
  // You can append it to an existing list or update a blog feed.
}
